## Task 2 – Digital Portfolio Reflection

In this task, I created and updated my profiles on GitHub, LinkedIn, and Kaggle to build a professional digital presence. Each of these platforms serves a unique purpose. GitHub is used to store and showcase coding projects, LinkedIn helps in building a professional network and connecting with peers and industry professionals, and Kaggle provides a platform to explore data science concepts and work with real-world datasets.

Through this task, I learned the importance of maintaining a clear and professional online identity. Setting up these profiles helped me understand how digital platforms can be used not only for learning but also for showcasing skills and achievements. It also made me more aware of how I present myself online.

In the next four years, I will keep updating my profiles by adding new projects, certifications, and skills. I aim to use GitHub to demonstrate my technical work, LinkedIn to build meaningful connections, and Kaggle to improve my analytical and problem-solving abilities.
